<h1 id=3D"id-06-IMSInformationSecurityCommunicationPlan-Purpose,scope,andta=
rgetaudience">Purpose, scope, and target audience</h1>
<p><strong>Purpose: </strong>This policy governs data protection=E2=80=93 a=
nd information security=E2=80=93related communications within AlpineAI.</p>
<p><strong>Scope: </strong>This policy applies to all communication channel=
s and any communication regarding information security or data protection.<=
/p>
<p><strong>Target audience: </strong>Defined in the <a href=3D"https://alpi=
neai.atlassian.net/wiki/x/AYBc" rel=3D"nofollow">Applicability Matrix</a>.<=
/p>
<h1 id=3D"id-06-IMSInformationSecurityCommunicationPlan-RelevantDocuments">=
Relevant Documents</h1>
<ul>
<li>
<p><a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://alpineaiag.sharepoint.com/:x:=
/s/AlpineAIAG/EW4FZgnVKyhKjAx1gMxxE70BpkIaeN3tLnz2NiLmwhZd2g?e=3Dw0itd9" re=
l=3D"nofollow">Customer Contacts for Information Security and Data Protecti=
on</a></p></li>
<li>
<p><a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://alpineaiag.sharepoint.com/:f:=
/s/AlpineAIAG/EslZk9Iv851ChwTJrlih6DQB8lkEuUEyMNu9Gqs2WJ9YvA?e=3DHJpYDH" re=
l=3D"nofollow">Inventory of Subprocessor Notifications</a></p></li>
</ul>
<h1 id=3D"id-06-IMSInformationSecurityCommunicationPlan-RelatedStandards&am=
p;Procedures">Related Standards &amp; Procedures</h1>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Section =E2=80=9C7.4 Communication=E2=80=9D of the ISO/IEC 27001:2022 st=
andard.</p></li>
</ul>
<h1 id=3D"id-06-IMSInformationSecurityCommunicationPlan-InternalCommunicati=
on">Internal Communication</h1>
<p><strong>Availability of policies.</strong> Information security and data=
 protection policies shall be available to employees on Confluence.</p>
<p><strong>Acknowledgements.</strong> Major versions of policies that requi=
re formal employee acknowledgement shall be hosted in Vanta, and employee a=
pprovals shall be recorded.</p>
<p><strong>Key decisions.</strong> Important information security and data =
protection decisions relevant to the entire team shall be communicated in m=
onthly meetings.</p>
<p><strong>Ad-hoc updates.</strong> Ad hoc decisions and relevant informati=
on shall be communicated directly (peer-to-peer or in groups via email or S=
lack).</p>
<h1 id=3D"id-06-IMSInformationSecurityCommunicationPlan-CommunicationwithCu=
stomers">Communication with Customers</h1>
<p><strong>Contacts in agreements.</strong> Data Protection Agreements shal=
l include the customer=E2=80=99s contact details for data protection and in=
formation security matters. If a dedicated contact is not specified, the ma=
in contractual contact shall be used.</p>
<p><strong>Inventory of Customer Contacts.</strong> Alpine AI shall maintai=
n a list of contacts for all customers to streamline communications require=
d for subprocessor change notifications, incident reporting and other relev=
ant matters. Key Account Management shall ensure that contact details remai=
n up to date.<br><em>Note: See section =E2=80=9CRelated Documents=E2=80=9D =
for the link to the Inventory of Customer Contacts.</em></p>
<p><strong>Subprocessor notifications.</strong> Notifications regarding cha=
nges to subprocessors shall be communicated in writing. The notification an=
d the recipient list shall be stored in SharePoint for traceability.<br><em=
>Note: See section =E2=80=9CRelated Documents=E2=80=9D for the link to the =
Inventory of Subprocessor Notifications.</em></p>
<h2 id=3D"id-06-IMSInformationSecurityCommunicationPlan-CommunicationwithAu=
thorities"><strong>Communication with Authorities</strong></h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Role as processor.</strong> With regard to customer data, Alpine=
 AI acts as a processor; the primary communication obligations rest with it=
s customers as controllers.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Coordination with customers.</strong> If an authority contacts A=
lpine AI, the company shall communicate only in collaboration with the cust=
omer and with the customer=E2=80=99s approval.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Incident reporting.</strong> Major incidents shall be reported t=
o authorities where there is a legal requirement to do so.</p></li>
</ul>
